Interface Summary
Argument An argument of a syntactic frame/semantic predicate
Component An element of multi-word terms decomposition
Condition A predicate used to describe a condition
Constituent A constituent indicates the phrase type of a node in a phrase structure tree
Definition A predicate used to give definitions
Edge An edge or arc in a phrase structure tree
Example A usage example for a given sense
FormVariant The predicate for a variant of a form
Frame A syntactic frame describing a syntactic behavior of an entry
LemonElement The super-class for all lemon elements (individuals)
LemonElementOrPredicate The superclass of all lemon elements/predicates (individuals/properties)
LemonPredicate Super class for all lemon predicates (properties)
LexicalEntry The lexical entry is the main representation of a term or word
LexicalForm A form of a lexical entry
LexicalSense A lexical sense indicates a meaning of an entry by mapping it to an ontology entity
LexicalTopic A topic for a lexicon or individual entry
LexicalVariant Predicate for variants between lexical entries
Lexicon A mono-lingual lexicon object composed of a set of lexical entries
MorphPattern A morphological inflection pattern of an entry
MorphTransform A single possible generation in a morphological pattern
Node A node in a phrase structure tree
Part A part of a word
Phrase A multiple word lexical entry
PhraseTerminal Abstract class for the range of leaf arcs
Property A property of a lemon element
PropertyValue A value of a given property
Prototype  
Representation The predicate for a representation of a form
SenseCondition An evaluable condition on entry/sense mapping.
SenseContext A pragmatic context in which a entry/sense mapping applies
SenseDefinition A definition of a given sense
SenseRelation A predicate used to relate senses
SynArg A predicate indicating the syntactic role of an argument
SyntacticRoleMarker The abstract class for markers that distinguished the syntactic role of an argument
Word A lexical entry that is a single word
